The paper deals with optimization problems related to vehicle routing, which is a classic topic in operations research and computer science. The use of regret as a measure of quality is a relatively new concept, and the paper proposes new formulations and algorithms for regret-bounded vehicle routing problems. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.GT (game theory), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), or cs.RO (robotics). Among these, cs.DS and cs.GT seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper involves the design and analysis of approximation algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems.
